'''Peter Kolchin''' is an American [[historian]].
==Life== He graduated from [[Columbia University]], and from [[Johns Hopkins University]] with a Ph.D. in 1970. He teaches at the [[University of Delaware]].<ref>http://www.udel.edu/History/bio/kolchin_peter.html</ref><ref>http://www.udel.edu/PR/UpDate/03/2/peter.html</ref>
==Awards== * 1988 [[Bancroft Prize]] in American History * 1988 [[Avery O. Craven Award]] from the [[Organization of American Historians]] <ref>http://www.oah.org/activities/lectureship/2009/lecturer.php?id=167</ref> * Charles Sydnor Award, [[Southern Historical Association]]
==Works== * {{cite book| title=First Freedom: The Responses of Alabama's Blacks to Emancipation and Reconstruction | publisher=University of Alabama Press | year=1972 }} (Revised Ed. 2008, ISBN 9780817355357) * {{cite book| title=Unfree Labor: American Slavery and Russian Serfdom| url=http://books.google.com/books?id=jv_0ZuuJk90C&printsec=frontcover&dq=inauthor:Peter+inauthor:Kolchin&cd=2#v=onepage&q=&f=false| publisher=Harvard University Press| year= 1987| isbn= 9780674920989 }} * American Slavery, 1619-1877 (1993, revised ed. 2003) ISBN 9780140241501 * {{cite book| title=A Sphinx on the American Land: The Nineteenth-Century South in Comparative Perspective| url=http://books.google.com/books?id=p-CSb2qNrUgC&printsec=frontcover&dq=inauthor:Peter+inauthor:Kolchin&cd=4#v=onepage&q=&f=false| publisher=LSU Press| year= 2003| isbn= 9780807128664 }}
*{{cite book| url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ykuhT3DFtdsC&printsec=frontcover&dq=inauthor:Peter+inauthor:Kolchin&cd=3#v=onepage&q=&f=false| chapter=Foreword| title=Up from Serfdom: My Childhood and Youth in Russia, 1804-1824| editor=Helen Saltz Jacobson| others=Translator Helen Saltz Jacobson| publisher=Yale University Press| year= 2002| isbn= 9780300097160 }} *{{cite book| url=http://books.google.com/books?id=eia0We-VnukC&pg=PA291&lpg=PA291&dq=Peter+Kolchin&source=bl&ots=TNomOXe3Bf&sig=Wai0AJm1Oq07uu3QiTiDIGWul0Q&hl=en&ei=akVBS5rhKsb8nAf9w630CA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=8&ved=0CBkQ6AEwBzge#v=onepage&q=Peter%20Kolchin&f=false| chapter=The Tragic Era? Interpreting Southern Reconstruction in Comparative Perspective | title=The Meaning of freedom: economics, politics, and culture after slavery| editors=Frank McGlynn, Seymour Drescher| publisher=University of Pittsburgh Press| year= 1992| isbn= 9780822954798 }}
